helix group at stanford welcome home people projects publications software training contact about directions opportunities department links intranet welcome the helix group at stanford is directed by russ altman and focuses on the creation and application of computational tools to solve problems in biology and medicine current application projects include the study of structure function relationships in macromolecular structure understanding the structure and folding of rna molecules and analyzing the relationship of genotype and phenotype particularly with respect to the response to drugs techniques used include knowledge representation database design machine learning natural language processing physics based simulation and graph based modeling analysis 2006 stanford university
